        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add recurring card scheduler",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds first-class recurring cards so operational work can run on a cadence through the existing card/run scheduler instead of through long-running loops or ad-hoc cron jobs.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Adds `schedule_json`, `next_run_at`, and `last_scheduled_run_at` card columns.\n- Adds an interval schedule helper with validation and next-run computation.\n- Allows `POST /api/cards` to accept a schedule, for example `{ \"kind\": \"interval\", \"everyMs\": 86400000 }`.\n- Wires recurring-card ticks into the existing Worker `scheduled()` handler.\n- Adds an owner-only `/api/admin/scheduler/tick` endpoint for manual scheduler ticks.\n- Documents recurring cards in the project docs/spec.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm run build`\n- `pnpm test`\n- `pnpm run lint`\n- `pnpm run format`\n",
